questions.explanationMd:
**Event delegation** leverages event bubbling by placing a single listener on a parent element instead of attaching listeners to each child.

Benefits:
- **Performance** — fewer event listeners means less memory usage
- **Dynamic elements** — works for elements added to the DOM after the listener was attached
- **Cleaner code** — one handler instead of many

```js
document.getElementById('list').addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  if (e.target.matches('li')) {
    console.log('Clicked:', e.target.textContent);
  }
});
```
